FT  10 DEC 92 / Councils may pull out of YT
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LISA WOOD, Labour Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
REPRESENTATIVES of English local authorities including London and the six
metropolitan areas have warned Mrs Gillian Shephard, the employment
secretary, that they may stop participating in Youth Training.
Since 1988, local authorities have been among the main providers of places
on the scheme, the main training programme for 16 to 19-year-olds, often
heavily subsidising them. Now they say the recession and government curbs on
spending will force them to curtail the scheme.
They believe the recession has invalidated many of the assumptions behind
YT.
