INDIA was gripped by a third day of violence yesterday, with the death toll
following the weekend destruction of the Ayodhya mosque rising above 700.
Police and troops were deployed in many cities in an attempt to suppress
continuing riots, arson attempts and stone-throwing attacks.
Worst-affected was Bombay, the commercial capital, where 150 have died. In
