recognised the importance of this huge capital investment to the long term
future of the Northern Ireland economy.'
The development is the centrepiece of the government's Laganside development
plan and will include a new concert hall to be financed by the Belfast City
Council, a 200-bedroom hotel, 400,000 sq ft of office space as well as
retail space and car parking. The complex will be located near the Belfast
City Hall.
Last month, Monarch Properties, the private property developer based in
Dublin, sold its 29.2 per stake in Ewart for 80p per share, having failed in
its attempt to take control of the board.
