FT  09 DEC 92 / Parliament and Politics: AEEU to raise party payments
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CATHY MILTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE AEEU electrical and engineering union yesterday announced a 14 per cent
increase in its contribution to the Labour party, Cathy Milton writes.
The increase of more than Pounds 100,000 is matched by a corresponding
increase in the notional number of members the union plans to affiliate to
Labour to 510,000 at Pounds 1.70 each. It will only partly offset the
decision last week by the TGWU general union to cut its contribution by
Pounds 500,000 and reduce affiliated members by more than 250,000 by 1994.
The move was agreed by the executive of the AEEU, formed by the recent
merger of the AEU engineering union and the EETPU electricians' union.
A review group is wrangling over the extent unions should influence party
elections and the annual conference.
The AEEU supports a move to one-member-one-vote for the party leadership and
selection elections while the TGWU would like to see the present electoral
college system survive broadly intact.
