The government's focus in drawing up its plans was on individuals in
greatest need and measures that had proved themselves successful, she said.
'We will give priority to those measures which help people the most.'
Opening the debate, Mr Frank Dobson, shadow employment secretary, placed his
emphasis on training, claiming that the government's training budget per
unemployed person was less than half of what it had been only 'three short
