<TEXT>
INTERNATIONAL mediators yesterday failed to get Bosnia's Moslem-led
government to talk to Mr Radovan Karadzic, the Bosnian Serb leader, agencies
report from Geneva.
Diplomats said Mr Cyrus Vance and Lord Owen, co-chairmen of the Geneva
conference on the former Yugoslavia, had asked Mr Haris Silajdzic, the
