capital of Sarajevo, made real progress virtually impossible in Geneva.
Fierce fighting broke out in Sarajevo yesterday, effectively cutting it off
from the outside world after clashes closed the main road to the airport and
the only other route into the capital from Serb-held Ilidza.
Serbs besieging Sarajevo yesterday offered free passage out to anyone
wishing to leave the city to avoid famine and cold.
