FT  09 DEC 92 / Europe's jobless rises 1.3m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LUXEMBOURG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE number of people out of work in the European Community rose to 14.6m in
October, up from 13.3m in October last year, the EC statistics office,
Eurostat, said yesterday, Reuter reports from Luxembourg.
Eurostat's monthly bulletin said the seasonally adjusted average rate of
unemployment also edged up to 9.8 per cent from 9.7 in September, and 9 per
cent in October 1991. It is now at the highest rate since June 1988.
Eurostat said the rise in the number of unemployed over the year was
particularly marked in Britain, Spain and eastern Germany, which together
accounted for 1.04m of the total increase.
