<HEADLINE>
FT  08 DEC 92 / UK Company News: Henderson in Pounds 42.5m expansion
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP COGGAN, Personal Finance Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
HENDERSON Administration has agreed to pay Pounds 42.5m cash for Touche
Remnant, its fellow fund management group. The two companies announced they
were in takeover talks in October.
As part of the deal, Societe Generale, Touche Remnant's current owner, has
agreed to take on the 22 year lease of TR's headquarters in London's Puddle
Dock.
The TR staff will transfer to Henderson's office in Finsbury Avenue;
Henderson estimates this will save Pounds 2.5m a year.
A condition of the deal is that Touche Remnant has net assets of Pounds
15.4m, and net cash (or its equivalent) of Pounds 18m, on acquisition.
The combined company will have about Pounds 9.9bn of funds under management,
of which a quarter will be in investment trusts - making the group the
biggest investment trust manager in the UK.
Mr Paul Manduca, Touche Remnant's chairman, will join the Henderson board
and will be deputy group managing director.
The acquisition circular shows that Touche Remnant incurred an operating
loss of Pounds 3.07m in 1991. Interest receivable of Pounds 2.4m reduced the
pre-tax loss to Pounds 668,000.
Henderson said that the takeover should bring considerable cost savings. Its
operating expenses are equivalent to 0.4 per cent of funds under management;
Touche Remnant's expenses represent 0.8 per cent.
The deal will have to be approved at an extraordinary meeting of Henderson
shareholders on December 21. Henderson's shares rose 47p to 685p yesterday.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
