<HEADLINE>
FT  08 DEC 92 / Rises for directors average 5% this year
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CATHERINE MILTON, Labour Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
COMPANY DIRECTORS' pay rises have averaged 5 per cent in the past 12 months
and are expected to slow to an average of 4 per cent in the coming year, a
survey by Reward Group and the Institute of Directors says.
The survey is believed to be the largest to date covering directors' pay. It
is published in the wake of the government's appeal to senior executives to
award themselves low pay rises and its announcement that public-sector
workers face a pay ceiling of 1.5 per cent. It shows that 16 per cent of
directors expect no increase.
Mr Blenyth Jenkins, IoD corporate affairs director, said: 'It is clear from
this survey that the large and apparently unjustified increases which have
recently attracted so much media attention are wholly unrepresentative.'
The survey of more than 6,000 directors shows that women directors averaged
7.1 per cent increases over the same period but continued to earn less than
their male peers.
Pay for managing directors working in London is nearly 20 per cent above the
national median while their counterparts in the south-west are paid 13 per
cent below the national median.
More than half of all directors received pay rises of 5 per cent or less and
35 per cent had rises of 4 per cent or less. Of those, 14 per cent received
no pay rise and 1 per cent accepted pay cuts.
The number of directors driving company cars has dropped from 84 per cent to
79 per cent over the past 12 months.
Pay appears to increase with company turnover and individual responsibility
levels. Managing directors of companies with turnover of more than Pounds
200m are paid an average of Pounds 107,500 plus a bonus worth Pounds 18,000.
More than 90 per cent have a company car.
The average salary for managing directors of companies turning over between
Pounds 20m and Pounds 250m is now Pounds 78,045, plus a bonus worth Pounds
11,000. More than 95 per cent have a company car, 29 per cent of them
Jaguars.
Managing directors of companies with turnovers of up to Pounds 25m are paid
an average of Pounds 46,000, plus a bonus worth Pounds 6,800. More than 95
per cent have a company car, with 13 per cent driving a Mercedes.
The Directors' Reward Survey. Reward Group, Reward House, Diamond Way, Stone
Business Park, Stone, Staffs. ST15 OSD. Pounds 350.
</TEXT>
