FT  08 DEC 92 / International Company News: New chief at Credit Suisse
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN RODGER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ZURICH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CREDIT SUISSE, Switzerland's third-largest bank, has chosen a young
investment banker to be its next chief executive.
Mr Josef Ackermann, 44, replaces Mr Robert Jeker, who is leaving the bank
'on the best of terms' to become managing director of Anova, Nueva and
Unotec, Mr Stephan Schmidheiny's three investment and holding companies.
