Swiss Bank Corporation. Both banks earlier this year saw their credit
ratings downgraded a notch from the cherished triple A by Moody's, the
rating service.
Mr Ackermann entered Credit Suisse in 1978, and has worked in corporate
banking in New York and in investment banking at Credit Suisse First Boston
in London.
Mr Jeker's departure helps ease the succession at the bank. Mr Rainer Gut,
the 60-year-old chairman, intends to stay until the retirement age of 68.
