FT  08 DEC 92 / Parliament and Politics: Lord Chancellor breaks deadlock
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Lord Chancellor, Lord Mackay, used his powers last night to resolve a
tied vote by peers. The 106-106 division came on a technical amendment on
procedure.
Tory Lord Aldington, chairman of the European committee, called for the body
to determine its own sub-committee structure as its work covered complex EC
documents. He moved a change to a report from the Lords liaison committee,
which regulates Upper House committees.
The Lord Chancellor, after the deadlock was announced, said the rules
provided that 'the question should be resolved in the negative unless there
is a majority in its favour' and he declared that the proposed change was
defeated.
